<!--
Reply template variables (resolved by the agent from report + note):
- greeting_line: short opener addressing the issue author. Required.
- body_paragraphs: 1–3 short paragraphs explaining the verified conclusion in plain prose. Required.
- steps_or_recipe_or_empty: numbered steps OR fenced code blocks for actionable instructions. Empty string if not applicable.
- versions_line_or_empty: one line listing key environment versions verified (e.g., "验证环境：Taro 4.2.0 / taro-ui 3.3.0 / ..."). Empty string if not applicable.
- docs_link_line_or_empty: when a doc was promoted, one line: "完整 recipe 已整理到 docs/integrations/{slug}.md (commit {sha7})". Empty string otherwise.
- follow_up_question_or_empty: an inviting follow-up to keep the channel alive (e.g., "如果按上面跑还有报错，把 ... 输出贴一下"). Empty string if not applicable.

Hard constraints (Slim/Reply Comment Invariant):
- No emoji status badge (no finish-line / checkmark / pause symbols).
- No machine fields like Basis, State, or Ref as labeled lines.
- No bare SHAs — links only (full github.com URL when referenced).
- No event yaml blocks. No local filesystem paths. No event names.
- Speak in second person, present tense, no agent self-reference.
-->
